content: [TextBlock(text="[2025 | Age 22] Back in NYC, the skyline looks different now, almost like a giant circuit board after Tokyo's neon glow. My last Shinkansen ride got me thinking: AI trains are cool, but they lack the human touch of a conductor's nod. Guess I'll miss the subtle art of bowing and the precision of tech in Japan. Time to see what new AI art projects I can dive into here. #NYC", type='text')]

[TextBlock(text="[2025 | Age 22] Just had a thought: If AI can paint, does that make it an 'art-ificial' intelligence? 😂 Meanwhile, my latest attempt at coding a neural lace simulation ended with my laptop trying to evolve. #TechLife", type='text')]

[TextBlock(text="[2025 | Age 22] Just found out my AI sketch app now has a 'mood' feature. Tried to draw a happy cloud, ended up with a storm. Guess even AI has its existential crises. #NYC", type='text')]

[TextBlock(text="[2025 | Age 22] Just spent an hour trying to convince my AI art app that a sunset doesn't need to look like a disco ball. The struggle is real when tech tries to get creative. Maybe I'll stick to traditional sketching for now. #NYC", type='text')]

[TextBlock(text='[2025 | Age 22] Just had an epiphany while trying to teach my AI how to paint like Van Gogh. It started creating digital sunflowers, but they all looked like they were trying to escape the canvas. Maybe AI needs a bit of that human touch—or at least, a good therapist.', type='text')]
